{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id8ee2e85d-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s290l–9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"290l–9"},"text":"§ 290l–9.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Capital increase","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id8ee2e85e-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s290l–9/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Subscription authorized","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id8ee2e85f-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s290l–9/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The United States Governor of the Bank may subscribe on behalf of the United States up to 90,044 additional callable shares of the capital stock of the Bank in accordance with Resolution No. 128 as adopted by the Board of Governors of the Bank on ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2010-05-14"},"text":"May 14, 2010","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id8ee2e860-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s290l–9/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Any subscription by the United States to additional capital stock of the Bank shall be effective only to such extent and in such amounts as are provided in advance in appropriations Acts.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id8ee2e861-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6","identifier":"/us/usc/t22/s290l–9/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Limitations on authorization of appropriations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In order to pay for the increase in the United States subscription to the Bank under subsection (a), there are authorized to be appropriated, without fiscal year limitation, up to $1,252,331,952 for payment by the Secretary of the Treasury.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id8ee2e862-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/513/tV/s562/c/12"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–513, title V, § 562(c)(12)","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/74/dI/tVII/s7081/e"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–74, div. I, title VII, § 7081(e)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-12-23"},"text":"Dec. 23, 2011","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/125/1260"},"text":"125 Stat. 1260","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id8ee2e863-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id8ee2e864-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id8ee2e865-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/74/dI/tVII/s7081/e"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–74, div. I, title VII, § 7081(e)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2011-12-23"},"text":"Dec. 23, 2011","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/125/1260"},"text":"125 Stat. 1260","children":[],"tail":", which directed amendment of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/513/s562/c"},"text":"section 562(c) of Pub. L. 101–513","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s290"},"text":"22 U.S.C. 290","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":" et seq.) by adding at the end a new par. (12), was executed to the second of two subsecs. (c) by adding this section, to reflect the probable intent of Congress. The first subsec. (c) of section 562 is set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s2293"},"text":"section 2293 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsecs. (a) and (b) were in the original (A) and (B), respectively, and pars. (1) and (2) of subsec. (a) were in the original (i) and (ii), respectively, and were editorially redesignated for purposes of codification.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
